oy with these simple soups that showcase fresh, seasonal ingredients. "},{"title":"15 Natural Flu Remedies to Ease Your Symptoms","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/15-natural-flu-remedies-to-ease-your-symptoms/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/naturalflu01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/naturalflu01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/naturalflu02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/naturalflu01-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/Eartheasy-Pinterest-.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/kelly-sikkema-475112-unsplash.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/kelly-sikkema-475112-unsplash-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/kelly-sikkema-475112-unsplash-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/11/naturalflu02-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-11-15 21:12:43","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":13376,"post_description":"The flu virus can make you feel miserable, attacking your stomach, throat, head, and sinuses. And while prescription drugs can help if taken right away, many natural remedies can soothe symptoms and stop you from getting sick in the first place. "},{"title":"Here\u2019s Why Washing Your Hair Could be Bad for You","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/heres-why-washing-your-hair-could-be-bad-for-you/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/shampoo01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/shampoo01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/shampoo02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/shampoo01-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/August-27-2018.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-08-27 19:02:51","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":13234,"post_description":"The average American uses nine personal care products on their hair, face, and body every day, together containing over 120 chemical ingredients. Most of us don\u2019t think twice about these products\u2019 effects on our health. The companies wouldn\u2019t be able to sell these products if they weren\u2019t safe, right?"},{"title":"More Than Another Water Emergency: PFAS Exposure and Your Health","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/more-than-another-water-emergency-pfas-exposure-and-your-health/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/wateremergency01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/wateremergency01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/wateremergency02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/wateremergency01-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/08/August-7-2018.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-08-03 18:50:07","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":13138,"post_description":"On July 30 the lieutenant governor of Michigan declared a state of emergency in Kalamazoo County after officials discovered that chemicals in drinking water were twenty times higher than levels recommended by the EPA. The city of Parchment, where the discovery was made, joined the list of other Michigan cities with a water supply contaminated by the chemicals PFOS and PFOA."},{"title":"This Dermatologist Tells the Real Truth About What You\u2019re Doing to Your Skin","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/this-dermatologist-tells-the-real-truth-about-what-youre-doing-to-your-skin/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/skincare01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/skincare01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/skincare02b.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/skincare03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/skincare01-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/July-30-2018.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/07/July-30-2018-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-07-23 20:16:48","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":13026,"post_description":"I don\u2019t know about you, but after a hard sweat session or some garden chores in the summer heat, I relish a good scrub in the shower. Clean, scrubbed skin feels so much better than the slimy sensation of sweat mixed with sunscreen, right?"},{"title":"What Keeps Mosquitoes Away? Mosquito Controls That Actually Work","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/what-keeps-mosquitoes-away-mosquito-controls-that-actually-work/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/mosquitocontrol01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/mosquitocontrol01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/mosquitocontrol02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Herbal-Armor-Spray-4oz-1003.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/mosquitocontrol01-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-06-19 16:48:44","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":12944,"post_description":"The lights are off. The covers are snug beneath your chin. You\u2019re falling blissfully into a long overdue sleep\u2014when you hear the high-pitched whine of an approaching mosquito. "},{"title":"3 Recipes That Will Make You Love Cooking With Lavender","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/3-recipes-that-will-make-you-love-cooking-with-lavender/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Lavender01_credit-Keller-Keller-Photography.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Lavender01_credit-Keller-Keller-Photography.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Lavender01_credit-Keller-Keller-Photography-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/\u00a9Alexandra-Grablewski_lavender02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/\u00a9Alexandra-Grablewski_lavender03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/credit-Keller-Keller-Photography_lavender04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Lavender01_credit-Keller-Keller-Photography-2.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-06-12 16:46:17","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":12888,"post_description":"In her recent book, Recipes from the Herbalist\u2019s Kitchen, Brittany Wood Nickerson notes how \u201cthere is a unique energy\u2014a nexus of power\u2014in the intersection between food and medicine.\u201d Here is the place where we unleash the potent healing properties found in our food simply by understanding the power of plant-based ingredients. "},{"title":"Are the Dangers of Asbestos Still Real?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/are-the-dangers-of-asbestos-still-real/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Emily-Walsh.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/Emily-Walsh.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/asbestos01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/10StageWVeg_BW_emerald.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/10StageWVeg_BW_emerald-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/06/asbestos01-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-06-05 17:52:08","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":12835,"post_description":"Although mining and production of asbestos in the United States came to an end more than a decade ago, the toxic mineral is still legal to use and imported regularly. "},{"title":"5 Books from 2017 That Will Help You Connect With Nature","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/5-books-from-2017-that-will-help-you-connect-with-nature/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/jonatan-pie-234237.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/jonatan-pie-234237.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/January-16-2018.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/5books01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/5books02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/5books03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/5books04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/5books05.jpg"],"post_date":"2018-01-16 19:54:53","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":10323,"post_description":"\u201cWildness is inescapable,\u201d said the writer Charles Foster. \u201cThe process of thriving as human beings, even in the middle of a throbbing metropolis, is to acknowledge the wild in you.\u201d Each year writers, researchers, and scientists dig into the fertile earth of nature to see what lessons they can glean from its wildness."},{"title":"Are There Microplastics in Your Drinking Water?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/are-there-microplastics-in-your-drinking-water/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/garbage-2729608.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/Nov-27-2017.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics01-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/garbage-2729608-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics03-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/microplastics04-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-11-24 19:24:58","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6753,"post_description":"As if there weren\u2019t enough scary pollutants in our drinking water, a recent study revealed that most of us drink microplastics everyday, in our coffee and tea, our soup, and sips from the water fountain. Worldwide 83% of water samples contained microplastics. In the U.S., an astonishing 94% of samples tested had microplastics."},{"title":"How to Make Delicious, Healing Bone Broth","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-make-delicious-healing-bone-broth/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/bonebroth1.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/bonebroth1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/bonebroth2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/bonebroth3.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-11-08 19:52:53","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6505,"post_description":"In recent years, bone broth has gone from being a vestige of your grandmother\u2019s stovetop to a healthful hipster craze. Stroll down the streets of Portland, London, or Vancouver and odds are you\u2019ll find broth bars serving up blends of golden liquid infused with all the flavors of an expensive wine. What\u2019s the attraction?\r\n"},{"title":"How to Take a Forest Bath","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-take-a-forest-bath/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/kristopher-roller-150754.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/kristopher-roller-150754.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/bas-van-velzen-346562.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/david-kovalenko-414247.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/aaron-burden-43446.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Forest-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/October-25-2017.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/kristopher-roller-150754-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/bas-van-velzen-346562-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/aaron-burden-43446-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/October-25-2017-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-10-25 15:46:30","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6444,"post_description":"Humans of the 21st century spend up to 87% of our lives inside, according to the Environmental Protection Agency. Yet scientific studies continue to demonstrate that contact with nature has significant benefits for our health. "},{"title":"The Environmental Cost of Legalizing Marijuana","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/the-environmental-cost-of-legalizing-marijuana/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/marijuana01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/marijuana01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-671493056.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-611886962.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/October-4-2017.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/marijuana02.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-10-04 21:17:10","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6362,"post_description":"As marijuana becomes legal in more states for medicinal and recreational purposes, the expanding industry has also increased its environmental footprint. Marijuana has been legalized in more than half of the United States, and Prime Minister Trudeau plans to make Canada the second country worldwide to legalize the substance at the national level."},{"title":"5 Easy Ways to Eat More Local Foods After Harvest Season","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/5-easy-ways-to-eat-more-local-foods-after-harvest-season/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/WinterLocalFood-01-skeeze.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/WinterLocalFood-01-skeeze.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/localfoods02_tim-mossholder.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/amelia-bartlett-176205.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/WinterLocalFood-04-ulleo.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/lewis-wilson-413627.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/September-14-2017.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-09-14 20:22:10","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6343,"post_description":"As awareness of the impact of modern food choices has spread, more of us have worked to <a href=\"https://eartheasy.local/articles/10-reasons-to-buy-food-locally/\" target=\"_blank\">source our food locally</a>. Some lucky folk live in climates where food grows abundantly year round and have little trouble eating locally in every season. Others live in areas where the ground is frozen solid for half the year, posing more of a challenge to our locavore lifestyle. How can you eat locally when the gardens and farms have frozen?"},{"title":"Using Essential Oils in Everyday Life","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/using-essential-oils-in-everyday-life/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils05.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/oils03-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Wordpress-Article-Styles_03.png","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Wordpress-Article-Styles_05.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Wordpress-Article-Styles_03-2.png"],"post_date":"2017-08-29 15:43:05","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2600,"post_description":"Aromatherapy is all about the therapeutic use of essential oils\u2014highly aromatic substances that occur naturally in plants."},{"title":"Do We Still Need Fluoride in Our Drinking Water?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/do-we-still-need-fluoride-in-our-drinking-water/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/water-2465437_preview.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/water-2465437_preview.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/les-jay-220845.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/dentist-pain-borowac-cure-52527.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/drew-taylor-235558.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/July-26-2017_preview.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/berkey-light-eartheasy_4.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-07-26 17:18:00","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6259,"post_description":"You\u2019ve no doubt been told by your dentist the importance of fluoride for preventing tooth decay. In addition to fluoride toothpaste, most dentists advise drinking fluoridated water to prevent cavities. Some pediatricians even recommend that kids whose water isn\u2019t fluoridated take fluoride supplements. However, recent studies have challenged the conventional wisdom that fluoridated water prevents tooth decay."},{"title":"Is Your Sunscreen Safe?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/is-your-sunscreen-safe/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/stanley-dai-287738.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/stanley-dai-287738.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/mike-wilson-191639.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/alexandre-perotto-46114.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/81TQYYDAY5L.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/81TQYYDAY5L-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/sai-kiran-anagani-209542.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/glen-jackson-301620.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/June-29-2017.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-06-29 22:16:35","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6188,"post_description":"Most of us have gotten the message that it\u2019s important to protect ourselves with sunscreen before heading out in the sun. What isn\u2019t yet as widely known are the potential dangers of many common sunscreens, both to ourselves and to aquatic life, which must contend with these chemicals when they wash off swimmers\u2019 skin."},{"title":"Foraging for Wild Teas: 9 Plants to Pick and Brew","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/foraging-for-wild-teas-9-plants-to-pick-and-brew/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/congerdesign.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/congerdesign.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Foraged-tea-02-Antranias.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Foraged-Tea-03-Hans.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Foraged-tea-04-takazart.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/vitoriocool.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/June-27-2017.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-06-27 21:51:50","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6166,"post_description":"A lot of us grew up thinking of tea as something that came in a bag. As foraging has regained popularity, more people are brewing their own herbal infusions from tea ingredients they harvest themselves, either from their own garden or from wild plants. Some may be familiar, but a number of delicious foraged tea ingredients might surprise you."},{"title":"Is Your Fish Dinner on Prozac?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/is-your-fish-dinner-on-prozac/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/pharma-4.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/pharma-4.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/pharma-7.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/pharma.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/pharma-3.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/June-23-2017-new.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-06-23 21:40:29","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6160,"post_description":"Most of us employ an \u2018out of sight, out of mind\u2019 mentality when we flush the toilet. But what about when you discover some of the things we flush are coming back to us through our drinking water?"},{"title":"How is Climate Change Threatening Your Health?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-is-climate-change-threatening-your-health/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/sky-404060_1920.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/sky-404060_1920.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/carbonemissions_AdamKedem.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Climate-and-Health-01-SD-Pictures.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-824085770.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Farm-to-Table.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Mar-23-2017.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-03-23 18:54:16","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4469,"post_description":"The climate made news on Tuesday when the World Meteorological Association (WMO) announced its annual findings in its State of the Climate Report. Not only was 2016 the hottest year on record, (0.06\u02daC above the previous record set in 2015), the year also included record concentrations of carbon dioxide in the atmosphere at 400 parts per million. Global sea ice dropped more than 4 million km2 below average, a development the WMO calls \u201can unprecedented anomaly.\u201d"},{"title":"Are You Too Connected?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/are-you-too-connected/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Too-Connected01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Too-Connected01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Too-Connected03-kaboompics.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Too-Connected04-nature-addict.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Mar-10-2017.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-03-10 20:48:18","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4909,"post_description":"I\u2019ve only recently joined the ranks of the billions of people with smartphones, and I quickly understood why these miraculous devices have become so popular. As long as I\u2019ve got my phone, I have a camera ready to snap a shot of any adorable moment in my kids\u2019 day \u2013 and text it to their grateful grandparents. I can get directions when I\u2019m lost, or look up the answer to virtually any question."},{"title":"Are Non-toxic Art Supplies Important for Your Health?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/are-non-toxic-art-supplies-important-for-your-health/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/ecoart01_RhondaK.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/ecoart01_RhondaK.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/ecoart02_TimArterbury.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Painting.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/ecoart03_AlvaroSerrano.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/ecoart04_NikMacmillan.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Mar-2-2017.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/03/ecoart01_RhondaK.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/03/ecoart02_TimArterbury.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/03/ecoart03_AlvaroSerrano.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/03/ecoart04_NikMacmillan.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-03-02 18:36:43","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4311,"post_description":"Whether you are a fine artist, a crafter, a parent, or a dabbler, you have probably experienced the highs and lows of an art project. But while it would be nice to create something that stands the test of time, let's hope doing art won't shorten your life or the life of the planet. To that end, it's good to be aware of the potential dangers of everyday art supplies and learn more about their alternatives. "},{"title":"5 Amazing Herbal Teas to Help You Beat the Flu","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/5-amazing-herbal-teas-to-help-you-beat-the-flu-2/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/herbal-tea.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/herbal-tea.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-636298530.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/StockSnap_3B4B5808A1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/vee-o-226.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/dandelion-tea.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/nettle-tea.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-02-03 06:45:38","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3040,"post_description":"Just when you think you've escaped, the flu can hit you like a brick. But before you run to the doctor or send your significant other to the store to wander haplessly through the aisles, remember: antibiotics don't work for viruses and most over-the-counter medications only treat the symptoms."},{"title":"The 10 Best Reasons to Get Outside this Winter","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/the-10-best-reasons-to-get-outside-this-winter/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-500388348.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-500388348.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Get-Outside-02-kachi.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Get-Outside-02-kachi-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Get-Outside-03-TheSource.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Get-Outside-03-TheSource-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Get-Outside-03-TheSource-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Get-Outside-01-langll.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/01/iStock-500388348.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/01/Get-Outside-02-kachi.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/01/Get-Outside-03-TheSource.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-01-18 23:07:54","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3286,"post_description":"The winters in Minnesota can be long and really cold, so appreciating the season can take some effort. To be honest, I could do without the -20 windchills and icy sidewalks that make getting anywhere a challenge. Plus, around here winter drags on for up to 6 months, so I don\u2019t always get as much time outside as I\u2019d like. "},{"title":"Walking: The Cure for What Ails You","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/walking-the-cure-for-what-ails-you/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/walking1.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/walking1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/hannah-donze-3494.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/walking2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/01/walking1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/01/hannah-donze-3494.jpg"],"post_date":"2017-01-12 21:40:26","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3104,"post_description":"The winter cold is setting in, the last of the holiday cheer is fading away, and in many parts of the country, there are more grey days than sunny ones. Your first instinct is to curl up with a good book and a warm cup of tea, but what you really need is a brisk walk. Rain or shine, a walk has some miraculous healing properties that even modern medicine can't rival."},{"title":"4 Simple Ways to Slow Down for the New Year","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/4-simple-ways-to-slow-down-for-the-new-year/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/genessa-panainte-179123.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/genessa-panainte-179123.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/daniel-monteiro-313651.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/hannah-donze-3494-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-598912704.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-12-28 23:47:16","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3809,"post_description":"With presents to wrap, parties to throw, and a house to decorate, the holiday season can be exceptionally hectic. As delightful as all these parties and events are, having too much on our schedules can leave us feeling drained and less jolly than we might like, especially by the time the New Year rolls around. Having busy schedules can also prevent us from enjoying these events in the first place."},{"title":"Supercharge Your Meals With Dehydrated Greens","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/supercharge-your-meals-with-dehydrated-greens/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens02-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Greens04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Greens04-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Greens04-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Greens04-3.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Greens04-4.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Greens04-5.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens05.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens05-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/greens05-2.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-10-29 00:25:01","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3755,"post_description":"You\u2019ve seen them in health food stores stocking shelves for winter: \u2018powdered greens\u2019 supplements replete with a long list of healthful ingredients guaranteed to boost your immunity, repair free radical damage, and improve overall mood and vitality. "},{"title":"Getting PCBs Out of Our Schools","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/getting-pcbs-out-of-our-schools/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/carlos-martinez-792.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/carlos-martinez-792.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/ryan-tauss-3826.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-533434790.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-10-20 16:54:23","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4281,"post_description":"Earlier this month, Senator Edward Markey (D-Mass.), America Unites for Kids, and the Environmental Working Group released reports about PCBs in school buildings across the United States. Their findings were based on research conducted by Harvard researcher Dr. Robert Herrick and revealed that up to 14 million students in the U.S. may be exposed to unsafe levels of PCBs."},{"title":"Veganism, Sustainability, and Punk Rock: Eartheasy Speaks with Joshua Ploeg","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/veganism-sustainability-and-punk-rock-eartheasy-speaks-with-joshua-ploeg/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/cavemoz.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/cavemoz.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/joshua.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/cavemoz-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-10-18 16:30:08","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":9541,"post_description":"When you think of combining music with food, what comes to mind?  Wine and cheese before the symphony?  Margaritas, tacos, and hot Latin jazz?  How about soymilk chai, vegan fare and punk rock?  Hmmm.  Perhaps not the most common of pairings. "},{"title":"Is Food Packaging Safe?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/is-food-packaging-safe/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-458577455.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-458577455.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/StockSnap_66TNA0T1AA.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/setwveggies.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-09-27 21:56:02","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":9355,"post_description":"Many of us choose organic in order to avoid exposure to chemicals. But even our organic cheese and beans come in packaging that may leach chemicals into our pesticide-free food. What\u2019s a health enthusiast to do?"},{"title":"Grow Your Own Medicine","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/grow-your-own-medicine/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-182175002.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-182175002.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/a-fox-101136.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-546165526.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-483750465.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/annie-spratt-40664.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/marko-blazevic-435245.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-06-28 22:43:46","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":9363,"post_description":"With the explosion of interest in alternative medicine and increasing numbers of resources available online, it\u2019s easier than ever to dabble in using herbals to support health and treat or prevent common ailments, from headaches and colds to insomnia and anxiety. "},{"title":"The Health Benefits of Getting Dirty","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/the-health-benefits-of-getting-dirty/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Kid-playing.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Kid-playing.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Muddy-kid.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/jordan-whitt-53084.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-05-31 21:59:05","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2655,"post_description":"You may have read about the myriad ways gardening supports good health, providing gentle exercise, vitamin D, and stress-busting contact with nature. It turns out that some of the most powerful health benefits of gardening may come from our contact with the soil itself."},{"title":"Grow Your Own Herbal Teas!","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/grow-your-own-herbal-teas/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/neven-krcmarek-330546.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/neven-krcmarek-330546.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/Shannon_headshot.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/herbaltea03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/herbaltea.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/manuela-bohm-329772.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/herbaltea05.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/herbaltea02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/herbaltea04.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-05-17 16:22:49","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":9399,"post_description":"\u201cThere is tea, and then there is tea,\u201d my grandmother used to say when she was drinking one of the many herbal concoctions I used to serve her during my university days. Raised from proud British stock, she only ever considered one beverage worthy of the moniker tea, and that was the one brewed from the plant <em>Camellia sinensis</em>. Her tea came in tins or boxes, and was first rolled, oxidized, and fermented to a dark chocolate brown before finding its way across oceans and into her pot. "},{"title":"Organic Meat and Milk Contain More Omega-3s","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/organic-meat-and-milk-contain-more-omega-3s/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jenny-hill-202522.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jenny-hill-202522.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-638601018.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/sebastian-lp-204232.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-03-29 17:24:44","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4617,"post_description":"Whether organically-raised foods are nutritionally superior has been a matter of debate for some time. While some studies have shown, for instance, that the concentration of nutrients in organic fruits and vegetables is higher than in their conventionally-grown counterparts, other studies have found otherwise. Two new meta-analyses focusing on organic milk and meat found that organic versions of these foods do in fact differ from conventional ones."},{"title":"The Toxic Stuff of Daily Life","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/the-toxic-stuff-of-daily-life/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/priscilla-du-preez-216790.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/priscilla-du-preez-216790.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-537462818.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/alexandra-gorn-308385.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-477120634.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-03-03 22:32:03","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3877,"post_description":"In May of last year, a document known as the Madrid Statement warned of the dangers of a class of common chemicals called poly- and perfluoroalkyl substances (PFASs), which are used in everything from water-repellant clothing to the lining of pizza boxes. Over 200 scientists registered their concern about the increasing amounts of these \u201chighly persistent\u201d compounds, which are found in the tissue and fluids of humans and animals worldwide."},{"title":"Can Vegan Cheese Help Shrink Your Foodprint?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/can-vegan-cheese-help-shrink-your-foodprint/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/brooke-lark-275181.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/brooke-lark-275181.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/edgar-castrejon-459811.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/annie-spratt-61214.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/brooke-lark-391764.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-626536634.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-02-23 17:54:52","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":9416,"post_description":"In researching the climate impact of food, I was dismayed to learn that though we ate very little meat (good climate move), the amount of cheese my family consumed was not so climate-friendly. With greater greenhouse gas emissions than fish, poultry, or pork, the cheese in our diets significantly upped the emissions of our otherwise relatively low-carbon lives."},{"title":"In Defense of Wheat","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/in-defense-of-wheat/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pexels-photo-209403.jpeg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pexels-photo-209403.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jonathan-petersson-322081-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/StockSnap_4S44NKUKIO-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pexels-photo-209403-1.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pexels-photo-209403-2.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/austin-ban-14522.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jonathan-petersson-322081-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/StockSnap_4S44NKUKIO-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/StockSnap_UQFSNYXB9C.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jonathan-petersson-322081-2-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/StockSnap_4S44NKUKIO-2-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-02-18 20:06:11","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4058,"post_description":"Confused about bread and its place in your life?  You\u2019re not alone.  More than 20% of Americans are trying to <a href=\"http://www.gallup.com/poll/184307/one-five-americans-include-gluten-free-foods-diet.aspx\">avoid gluten</a>, though their reasons range from the relatively uncommon diagnosis of Celiac Disease, to a wide range of ambiguous health symptoms, to a vague media-generated sense that \u201cgluten-free\u201d means healthier. "},{"title":"How to Drink Water After Flint","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-drink-water-after-flint/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-523615224.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-523615224.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-506793604.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-157562359.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Berkey-Light-Daytime.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-522471372.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-02-09 22:41:18","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5004,"post_description":"Water.  It\u2019s in our soup, in our coffee, in our bathtubs and our baby bottles.  When it\u2019s clean and abundant, we take it for granted.  Even if you\u2019ve never been to Michigan, you\u2019re probably feeling for the people of Flint.  Their betrayal hits hard.  Americans are raised to feel uncommonly safe and protected.  Like most affluent \u201cfirst world\u201d nations, our government agencies and public utilities are assumed to be competent, transparent, and trustworthy."},{"title":"Zika Virus 'Spreading Explosively,' What You Need to Know","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/zika-virus-spreading-explosively-what-you-need-to-know/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/theodore-moore-336083.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/theodore-moore-336083.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/freestocks-org-71789.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/liv-bruce-270665.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/lucas-sankey-302618.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/killian-pham-147972.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2016/02/hans-vivek-223133.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-02-04 22:31:43","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5605,"post_description":"What is Zika? The Zika virus was discovered decades ago in the Zika forest of Uganda, and because symptoms of infection are typically mild \u2013 80% of those infected don\u2019t even have symptoms \u2013 researchers have not paid much attention to it. Carried by mosquitoes, Zika recently migrated to the Americas, where populations have not built up immunity, allowing it to spread quickly. "},{"title":"Can Happiness Save the World? Self-Help in Urgent Times","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/can-happiness-save-the-world-self-help-in-urgent-times%e2%80%a8/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/daniel-mingook-kim-139409.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/daniel-mingook-kim-139409.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/blubel-103316.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/alexander-dummer-150646.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/StockSnap_F6C12E015C.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-501000512.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/adrian-williams-76618.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-02-02 19:29:52","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4896,"post_description":"After rising to prominence with No Impact Man, a chronicle of his year-long experiment to live as greenly as possible in New York City, writer Colin Beavan says he\u2019s figured out how to \u201chave it all\u201d: a comfortable, fun life AND the satisfaction of \u201cdoing good\u201d for the planet.  With his recent book <em>How to Be Alive</em>, he\u2019s ready to start a movement of \u201clifequesters\u201d who reject \u201cstandard life approaches\u201d in favor of finding their own truth."},{"title":"Should We Be Eating Insects?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/should-we-be-eating-insects/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Eating_Bugs1\u00a9Livinfarms.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Eating_Bugs1\u00a9Livinfarms.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Eating_Bugs2\u00a9LivinFarms.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Eating_Bugs3\u00a9Livinfarms.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-01-28 22:20:20","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4986,"post_description":"Sometimes solutions to the world\u2019s toughest problems are right under our noses\u2014or that\u2019s what innovators from Europe and North America seem to be discovering in their hunt for global food security. In recent years, impending protein shortages and the lack of sustainable food production models have led more than one innovator to the practice of entomophagy, otherwise known as eating insects. Could they</br> be onto something?"},{"title":"Is Radon an Unseen Hazard in Your Home?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/is-radon-an-unseen-hazard-in-your-home/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jesse-roberts-146556.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jesse-roberts-146556.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-517004922.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-185239897.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-186810336.jpg"],"post_date":"2016-01-26 19:48:41","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4649,"post_description":"Though you can\u2019t see, smell, hear, or feel it, radon nonetheless poses a significant risk to human health. This naturally occurring radioactive gas comes from uranium, found in nearly all soils, and infiltrates our homes through cracks in foundations. Radon can become trapped in our houses and build to unhealthy levels if not remediated."},{"title":"How to Reduce Lead Hazards in Your Home","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-reduce-lead-hazards-in-your-home/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jon-moore-400422.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jon-moore-400422.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/nolan-issac-38303.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-531913206.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/caleb-woods-269348.jpg"],"post_date":"2015-09-10 17:59:49","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4882,"post_description":"Lead contamination can seem like a problem we solved long ago, when we wisely outlawed lead in gasoline and paint and stopped using lead pipes. However, like many widely used industrial materials, lead is pretty persistent in the environment and remains a danger if you don\u2019t take precautions. Why should lead merit your attention? Even at low levels, lead can have significant neurological effects. "},{"title":"Allergens in Natural Beauty Products","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/allergens-in-natural-beauty-products/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-476468679.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-476468679.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-512322151.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/alice-young-216434.jpg"],"post_date":"2015-03-26 17:43:24","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3380,"post_description":"Women want to be beautiful.  The cosmetic market is saturated with products that promise to make us look younger and more radiant, yet many of these assurances of beauty also come with the reality of harsh chemicals from a test tube.  Taking this into consideration, it is easy to understand why women often look toward natural beauty products as a safer alternative."},{"title":"Stop Killing the Microbes that Keep Us Healthy: 5 Strategies","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/stop-killing-the-microbes-that-keep-us-healthy-5-strategies/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-628978952.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-628978952.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-458545237.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/freestocks-org-126848.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/click-images-133817.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jakub-kapusnak-296881.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/Kid-playing.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-644474058.jpg"],"post_date":"2015-03-24 18:42:01","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4335,"post_description":"It\u2019s a perspective shift.  As living creatures, we see ourselves members of a large ecosystem, however, we each also contain an ecosystem.  Our bodies each host more than 100 trillion microbes, going about their daily business on every inch of our skin and much of our insides.  These minuscule life forms outnumber our own cells by about 10 to 1, which is a good argument to begin using the royal \u201cWe\u201d to refer to oneself."},{"title":"Healing Gardens","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/healing-gardens/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-471684151.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-471684151.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pepe-nero-229539.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/joshua-ness-109303.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/colin-maynard-150097.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/sora-sagano-103742.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/dimitri-tyan-261850.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/dimitri-tyan-261850-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/03/pepe-nero-229539.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/03/pepe-nero-229539-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/03/joshua-ness-109303.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/03/colin-maynard-150097.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/03/sora-sagano-103742.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/03/dimitri-tyan-261850.jpg"],"post_date":"2015-03-12 16:40:23","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4390,"post_description":"\u201cThere is new life in the soil for every man. There is healing in the trees for tired minds and for our overburdened spirit, there is strength in the hills, if only we lift up our eyes. Remember that nature is your great restorer.\u201d Calvin Coolidge"},{"title":"Systemic Pesticides and Food Health","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/systemic-pesticides-and-food-health/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pexels-photo-257840.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/pexels-photo-257840.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/emre-gencer-31502.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/erica-modugno-6218.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/james-pritchett-3917-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/james-pritchett-3917-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-471824579.jpg"],"post_date":"2015-02-03 21:34:52","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3080,"post_description":"When, exactly, did a bowl of grapes on a buffet table become cause for suspicion, rather than delight?  Increasingly, we\u2019re not afraid to ask \u201care those organic?\u201d before taking a bite.  If the answer is no, we may pass on to the next item. "},{"title":"Natural Remedies for Winter Depression (Seasonal Affective Disorder)","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/natural-remedies-for-winter-depression-seasonal-affective-disorder/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/silvestri-matteo-176500.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/silvestri-matteo-176500.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/greg-rakozy-207204.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/jay-wennington-2250.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/alisa-anton-177720.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/isaac-wendland-47362.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/matt-hoffman-146094.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/annie-spratt-207740.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2015/01/alex-hockett-42938.jpg"],"post_date":"2015-01-23 00:39:34","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2801,"post_description":"As daylight hours wane and the northern hemisphere tilts away from the sun, plants and animals make their instinctual seasonal preparations.  Biological changes transform the landscape: deciduous trees shed leaves to conserve energy and enter dormancy; certain birds emerge in new seasonally-appropriate plumage, while others migrate southward. "},{"title":"10 Steps to Make (And Keep) an Effective New Year's Resolution","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/10-steps-to-make-and-keep-an-effective-new-years-resolution/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/badder-manaouch-246249.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/badder-manaouch-246249.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/daiga-ellaby-233070.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/glenn-carstens-peters-190592.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/rawpixel-com-191102.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/christian-kaindl-332935.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/chaz-mcgregor-310853.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/rawpixel-com-192251.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/curtis-macnewton-12711.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/yutacar-28290.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/chuttersnap-135797.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/markus-spiske-139525.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/12/charles-koh-365288.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-12-29 18:12:34","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5675,"post_description":"Out with the old, in with the new!  The calendar year turns, and all around the world we reflect upon the past twelve months and make wishes about our upcoming \u201ctrip around the sun\u201d.  A new year, like a birthday, can startle us with the tangible passing of time: our days are limited and precious."},{"title":"11 Common Foods to Avoid During Pregnancy","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/11-common-foods-to-avoid-during-pregnancy/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_HJ8M7LUVLT.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_HJ8M7LUVLT.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/alex-munsell-18754.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_CCBWIQCNEJ.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/iStock-476512570.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/caroline-attwood-301746.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/roberta-sorge-157246.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/roberta-sorge-157246-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/roberta-sorge-157246-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/roberta-sorge-157246-3.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/roberta-sorge-157246-4.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/iStock-458577455.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/iStock-458577455-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/iStock-479541866.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/andrew-ridley-185915.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/jonathan-forage-225346.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/francesco-gallarotti-134632.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/brigitte-tohm-107901.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-12-04 21:00:13","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":817,"post_description":"At your very first prenatal visit, you may be given lists of anxiety-inducing \u201cdon\u2019ts\u201d from your well-meaning medical provider.  Don\u2019t handle cat litter \u2014 it can carry toxoplasmosis.  Don\u2019t eat undercooked eggs to avoid salmonella, and stay away from brie and other soft cheeses which have been linked to listeria."},{"title":"Can Dementia be Prevented by Diet and Lifestyle?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/can-dementia-be-prevented-by-diet-and-lifestyle/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/nathalia-bariani-100947.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/nathalia-bariani-100947.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/alex-blajan-105349.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/Cherry-tomatoes.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/dylan-richards-252573.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/joyce-huis-280682.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/cristian-newman-290588.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/erol-ahmed-407736.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/agto-nugroho-392793.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/iStock-692145800.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2014/11/filipe-almeida-191584.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-11-11 23:30:16","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5439,"post_description":"As we grow older, many of us begin losing sleep over the looming possibility of developing Alzheimer\u2019s or other forms of dementia.  Ironically, both sleep problems and anxiety increase our risk profile for developing these conditions. Especially if we\u2019ve cared for a parent or other relative with dementia, we want to feel like we have the power to change our own fate.  "},{"title":"How to Choose Earth-Friendly Edible Oils","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-choose-earth-friendly-edible-oils/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/StockSnap_Z7UAMJU01N.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/StockSnap_Z7UAMJU01N.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/anahi-martinez-322194.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-594029004.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-576732962.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-06-18 20:21:21","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":1640,"post_description":"Like any food product, there are oils that are produced more sustainably than others, and those that are better for our health. There is usually a lot of processing involved in the production of oils before they reach your kitchen, from where the oils come from, to how it is metabolized in our bodies, to where and how long to store it, </br>and oh yes, how it tastes!"},{"title":"Teaching Your Child to Love Vegetables","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/teaching-your-child-to-love-vegetables/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-612261820.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-612261820.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-114332874.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-467635266-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-613765102.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-06-10 21:47:58","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4792,"post_description":"In Dr. Seuss\u2019s Green Eggs and Ham, cajoling your kids with every outlandish trick you can muster: \u201cWould you eat them in a box? Would you eat them with a fox?\u201d In the name of the elusive \u201cbalanced diet\u201d, we\u2019ve all engaged in parenting strategies we\u2019d rather not confess. Nowhere else are the power-struggles of the parent/child relationship laid so bare."},{"title":"How to Remove Fluoride from Water","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-remove-fluoride-from-water/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/Faucet.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/Faucet.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/Berkey-Light-Daytime.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/Big-Berkey.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/06/iStock-538170002.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-05-22 20:42:43","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":650,"post_description":"In 1945, Grand Rapids, Michigan became the first US city to fluoridate the public water supply.\u00a0 The idea quickly caught on, and the controversy\u00a0began soon after: in growing numbers, a vocal minority has raised concerns about fluoride\u2019s role in a broad range of health problems."},{"title":"How to Use Nettles with Your Springtime Cooking","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-use-nettles-with-your-springtime-cooking/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle01.jpeg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle01.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle01-1.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle01-2.jpeg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle05.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/nettle06.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-05-01 04:22:08","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2108,"post_description":"Nettles have been on earth longer than humans\u2014we just forgot about them for a few generations.\u00a0 A century ago, rural cooks prized wild plants.\u00a0 Foraging was a daily domestic routine, a tradition and a necessity."},{"title":"Evidence Grows Linking Autism with Pollution","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/evidence-grows-linking-autism-with-pollution/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-598827520.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-598827520.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-639893612.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/Coal-01-MonikaP-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/city-1283844.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-04-04 22:33:12","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5023,"post_description":"For years, parents have traded stories online, seeking answers about their child\u2019s mysterious disability.\u00a0 This month, a newly published analysis\u00a0shows the strongest correlation yet between autism and prenatal exposure to pollution.\u00a0 Other smaller studies previously suggested a connection, but science is cautious to confirm findings until the results can be repeated in larger-scale projects."},{"title":"8 Common Products Expecting Moms Should Avoid","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/8-common-products-expecting-moms-should-avoid/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-638572636.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-638572636.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-458577455.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/freestocks-org-209882.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-513491906.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/justin-schuler-253611.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/justin-schuler-253611-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-615915652.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-03-18 21:56:36","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2624,"post_description":"A pregnant woman gets plenty of well-meaning advice \u2014 everyone in the check-out line offers an opinion about her diet, her weight, and which parenting philosophy she should read up on. \u00a0But it\u2019s easy to overlook some items considered \u201cnecessities\u201d of daily life, though investigating their ingredients reveals cause for unease. \u00a0"},{"title":"After Fukushima - Is It Safe to Eat Pacific Seafood?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/after-fukushima-is-it-safe-to-eat-pacific-seafood/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jakub-kapusnak-296868.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jakub-kapusnak-296868.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-481671624.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/erwan-hesry-209418.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jonathan-forage-225346.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/jonathan-forage-225346-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-02-27 19:15:54","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3927,"post_description":"Following the catastrophic failure of the Fukushima Dai-ichi nuclear plant on March 11, 2011, many of us found another reason to lose sleep. \u00a0Nearly three years later, news of the unfolding disaster alternately overwhelms us and falls strangely silent. \u00a0Conflicting opinions, theories, and \u201cfacts\u201d each offer to enlighten, reassure, or terrify."},{"title":"How to Make a Winter Soup to Boost Your Immune System","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/how-to-make-a-winter-soup-to-boost-your-immune-system/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/wintersoup01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/wintersoup01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/wintersoup02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/wintersoup03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/wintersoup04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/wintersoup05.jpg"],"post_date":"2014-01-22 04:44:19","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2093,"post_description":"Making soup is a healing practice.  It starts with the simple intention to nourish and nurture ourselves and our loved ones.  This soup can come together in an hour, but its effect on the body and soul are a world away from the quick-fixes of take-out food or frozen entrees."},{"title":"FDA to Phase Out Trans Fats in Processed Foods","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/fda-to-phase-out-trans-fats-in-processed-foods/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jessica-henderson-365335.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jessica-henderson-365335.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/clem-onojeghuo-206832.jpg"],"post_date":"2013-12-06 18:16:45","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4609,"post_description":"The Food and Drug Administration initiated a process today which will most likely result in the banning of trans fats in all food products sold in the US. For over a decade, scientific consensus has been building over the dangers of trans fats which are used to improve the taste and texture of many processed food products, and to increase product shelf life. The artery-clogging properties of trans fats have been shown to increase levels of LDL \u201cbad\u201d cholesterol, while lowering levels of HDL \u201cgood\u201d cholesterol."},{"title":"Eight Easy-To-Find Superfoods","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/eight-easy-to-find-superfoods/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/lior-mazliah-111379.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/lior-mazliah-111379.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2013/10/jakub-kapusnak-296865.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2013/10/matthew-hamilton-160833.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2013/10/charlotte-coneybeer-183671.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2013/10/nick-sarro-139765.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2013/10/jakub-kapusnak-296865-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2013/10/Ben-Greenfield-Forest2.jpg"],"post_date":"2013-10-21 18:29:04","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5526,"post_description":"You\u2019ve no doubt witnessed the \u201csuperfood\u201d trend sweeping across the health world. From Peruvian maca maca fruit to Chinese hemp seeds to Tibetan gogi berries, these crazy and exotic compounds are currently the darling of magazines and food blogs everywhere."},{"title":"Smart Seafood Choices: How to be an Informed Seafood Consumer","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/smart-seafood-choices-how-to-be-an-informed-seafood-consumer/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/bodie-pyndus-57646.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/bodie-pyndus-57646.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/caroline-attwood-301746.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/jonathan-forage-225346.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/aman-bhargava-268339.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/agto-nugroho-392793.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/james-wei-146792.jpg"],"post_date":"2013-05-16 21:20:54","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5392,"post_description":"Doctors recommend fish over beef, mutton and pork for healthy human protein consumption. Yet, with global warming and ocean acidification, can the oceans sustain more harvesting of fish? Seafood plays an important role in a balanced diet. High in Omega-3s, which boost immunity and reduce the risk of heart disease, stroke, cancer and other ailments, seafood is especially important for pregnant and nursing women and young children."},{"title":"Certified Organic: What Does It Mean?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/certified-organic-what-does-it-mean/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/tim-mossholder-2139.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/tim-mossholder-2139.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/annie-spratt-143539.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/StockSnap_D0C5D92CD9.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/keilidh-ewan-196889.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-529661632.jpg"],"post_date":"2013-04-11 16:55:17","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4705,"post_description":"My friend Ruth couldn\u2019t come to sauna the other night. She said she had food poisoning from the nitrates in the bacon she had eaten earlier in the day. I looked up nitrates and learned that sodium nitrate and sodium nitrite are used to keep red meat looking red, and with limited scientific proof, to inhibit botulism. The nitrates wouldn\u2019t have been in the bacon had it been certified organic."},{"title":"Cancer-causing chemical found in drinking water of 31 U.S. cities","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/cancer-causing-chemical-found-in-drinking-water-of-31-u-s-cities/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/iStock-513491906.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/iStock-513491906.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-12-22 03:57:38","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":11272,"post_description":"Study results released today by the Environmental Working Group (EWG) report that hexavalent chromium, the cancer-causing chemical made famous by the film \u201cErin Brockovich,\u201d has been detected in the tap water of 31 of the 35 U.S. cities tested."},{"title":"4 Tips for Safe, Effective Sunscreen Use","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/4-tips-for-safe-effective-sunscreen-use/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-539480858.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-539480858.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-500579999.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/leo-rivas-micoud-130488-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-500579999-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-539480858-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-539480858-2-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-05-18 22:01:45","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3602,"post_description":"It seems the more research that goes into the safety and effectiveness of sunscreens, the more confusing it is for consumers to use these formulations with confidence. "},{"title":"Link Found Between Air Pollution and Childhood Obesity","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/link-found-between-air-pollution-and-childhood-obesity/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/freestocks-org-70276.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/freestocks-org-70276.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/freestocks-org-73878-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-04-30 20:22:17","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5754,"post_description":"The underlying causes of obesity in the US have long been attributed to poor diet and lack of exercise, but the results of a recent study at Columbia University indicate that air pollution also contributes to obesity in children. Children born to women who were exposed to higher levels of certain air pollutants during pregnancy were nearly twice as likely to become obese by age 5 than children of mothers with lower levels of exposure. "},{"title":"\u201cNon-Toxic\u201d Nail Polishes Found to Contain Toxins","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/non-toxic-nail-polishes-found-to-contain-toxins/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2012/04/abbie-bernet-251310.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2012/04/abbie-bernet-251310.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2012/04/sabina-ciesielska-325340.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2012/04/biel-morro-128513.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2012/04/tiko-giorgadze-258590.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2012/04/tiko-giorgadze-250881.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-04-16 18:31:47","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5725,"post_description":"I don\u2019t wear nail polish, it simply doesn\u2019t appeal to me. And fancy nails don\u2019t go with gardening, which does appeal to me. But every time I go to Sacramento to visit my mom and sister, the first thing they do is invite me to the local nail salon to get a manicure and pedicure. I\u2019m a country girl coming to town and they see some rough edges that need smoothing. I realize they want to give me a treat, so I go along</br> with the program."},{"title":"Are Children Spending Enough Time Outdoors?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/are-children-spending-enough-time-outdoors/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/luke-brugger-30428.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/luke-brugger-30428.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/Kid-in-nature.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-532578130.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-04-13 22:14:46","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2195,"post_description":"\u201cIn my 40+ years of observing families, the single biggest change I have seen is that children are not outside playing like they used to,\u201d said Nell Trayhill, a retired family therapist from South Carolina. Standing behind me on line at an airport ticket counter last month, Mrs. Trayhill seemed happy to have my ear."},{"title":"Swallowing Our Pride","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/swallowing-our-pride/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-458131153.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-458131153.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-02-22 18:23:31","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5879,"post_description":"Extremes of achievement have always fascinated us. The Guinness Book of Records has made a fortune documenting the outer boundaries of human experience with the implicit message that competition brings out the best in all of us, unlocking our pent up potential. While many of the Guinness records are indeed worthy acknowledgements of human accomplishment, some are testament to low points in the human experience."},{"title":"Microscopic Plastic Particles May Be Entering Food Chain","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/microscopic-plastic-particles-may-be-entering-food-chain/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-484218282.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-484218282.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-685511930.jpg"],"post_date":"2012-02-06 22:24:28","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4571,"post_description":"Plastic particles less than 1mm, defined as \u2018microplastics\u2019, have been steadily accumulating in marine environments across the globe. Studies of shoreline debris at 18 different locations worldwide have identified small, fibrous particles of plastic which are washed up on beaches, embedded in sediments and even found in cell tissues of marine organisms."},{"title":"Are You Feeding Your Kids Twinkies For Breakfast?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/are-you-feeding-your-kids-twinkies-for-breakfast/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/david-streit-228657.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/david-streit-228657.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/freestocks-org-122528.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-12-12 19:50:46","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5538,"post_description":"We all know it\u2019s the sugar in children\u2019s cereals that makes them popular. And cereal makers, more than anyone, are aware of the singular appeal of sugar amid the myriad of ingredients in today\u2019s breakfast cereals. Parents may indulge their children with sugary cereals from time to time, but most parents would forbid a breakfast diet of Twinkies or chocolate chip cookies."},{"title":"BPA Levels Spike with Canned Soup","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/bpa-levels-spike-with-canned-soup/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/cala-150730-1.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/cala-150730-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/arshad-pooloo-345648.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/DSCN10341.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-11-29 00:27:56","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6068,"post_description":"Surprising results from a recent study at the Harvard School of Public Health have shown that volunteers who consumed one serving of canned soup a day for five days had a more than 1,200 percent increase in urinary BPA (Bisphenol A) over people who consumed fresh soup for the same period. The authors say their study is one of the few to measure human BPA levels after consuming</br> canned products."},{"title":"Why TV for Children Under Two is a Bad Idea","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/why-tv-for-children-under-two-is-a-bad-idea/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren03.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren03-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren02-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren01-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/tvchildren01-2.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-10-25 23:19:30","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2403,"post_description":"Researchers are using the scientific approach to establish what many parents know intuitively \u2013 children under two years of age should not be watching TV."},{"title":"The Healing Power of a Walk in the Woods","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/the-healing-power-of-a-walk-in-the-woods/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/woods01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/woods01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/woods02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/woods03.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-07-06 04:35:57","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2119,"post_description":"For over 20 years, I walked to work each morning along a winding trail through a forest of giant cedar and fir trees, my mind usually preoccupied with the challenges of helping run</br> a small woodworking business."},{"title":"7 Easy Ways to Reduce Your Exposure to Formaldehyde","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/7-easy-ways-to-reduce-your-exposure-to-formaldehyde/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/alexander-dummer-150646.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/alexander-dummer-150646.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/justin-schuler-253611.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Q67DPDQSC1.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-06-20 23:50:54","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":1122,"post_description":"On June 10, 2011, the National Toxicology Program released its 12th Report on Carcinogens, which added formaldehyde to its list of carcinogens, and said it is found in \u2018worrisome quantities\u2019 in plywood, particle board, mortuaries and hair salons."},{"title":"WHO: Cell Phone Emissions May Cause Cancer","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/who-cell-phone-emissions-may-cause-cancer/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/maliha-mannan-63635.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/maliha-mannan-63635.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/matthew-kane-71727.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-06-02 23:04:32","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6062,"post_description":"Cell phones have become such an integral part of our daily lives that it\u2019s natural to want to dismiss warning of potential health hazards associated with their use. But a new advisory issued from the World Health Organization may cause us to reconsider how we use cell phones, and whether these devices should be used</br> at all by young people. "},{"title":"Prenatal Pesticide Exposure Linked to Lower IQs in Children","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/prenatal-pesticide-exposure-linked-to-lower-iqs-in-children/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/freestocks-org-73878.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/freestocks-org-73878.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/StockSnap_HJ8M7LUVLT.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/emre-gencer-31502.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-04-27 18:28:46","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5181,"post_description":"Pregnant women, while still encouraged to eat fruit and vegetables as part of a healthy diet, should wash produce thoroughly before eating, or better yet, buy organic produce. This advice comes in the wake of three new studies linking prenatal exposure to pesticides with lower IQs in children. Pesticides classified as organophosphates are primarily used to treat agricultural crops, and to a lesser extent can be found in yard and garden pest control products."},{"title":"5 Tips to Reduce Your Exposure to BPA and Other Hormone Disrupting Chemicals in Your Diet","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/5-tips-to-reduce-your-exposure-to-bpa-and-other-hormone-disrupting-chemicals-in-your-diet/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/caroline-attwood-243834.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/caroline-attwood-243834.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/clem-onojeghuo-108720.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/ali-inay-9858.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-04-07 16:26:12","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4693,"post_description":"Adults and children can reduce their exposure to hormone-disrupting chemicals, including bisphenol-A (BPA), by eating more fruits and vegetables and less food from plastic containers and metal cans, according to a recent study. A group of 20 San Francisco residents had 66% less BPA in their urine after spending three days on a diet of fresh, organic and unpackaged food, scientists found."},{"title":"6 Tips for Safer Cell Phone Use","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/6-tips-for-safer-cell-phone-use/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/cellphone01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/cellphone01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/cellphone02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/cellphone02-1.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-03-24 01:27:22","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2509,"post_description":"As developments in cell phone technology leap forward, the studies of potential health impacts associated with cell phone use present confusing and inconclusive results. "},{"title":"Cadmium in Kids\u2019 Jewelry May Pose Poison Risk","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/cadmium-in-kids-jewelry-may-pose-poison-risk/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/DSC_2206.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/DSC_2206.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/kelly-sikkema-203594.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/niklas-tidbury-317842.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-03-22 20:06:12","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5979,"post_description":"Editor\u2019s Note: I fail to understand why parents put jewelry on babies, or give toy jewelry to young children. Children don\u2019t need jewelry to enhance their natural beauty. And indulging a young child with cheap trinkets introduces them to the concept of consumerism as a false standard of beauty and status. "},{"title":"Eco-impact of wild seafood less than that of poultry, beef","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/eco-impact-of-wild-seafood-less-than-that-of-poultry-beef/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/erwan-hesry-209418.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/erwan-hesry-209418.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/jakub-kapusnak-296868.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-02-11 03:42:36","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":11267,"post_description":"At a recent Seafood Summit in Vancouver, B.C., Professor Ray Hilborn, Ph.D., a world-famous fisheries researcher from the University of Washington\u2019s School of Aquatic and Fishery Sciences, described his encouraging conclusions about the relative ecological impacts of land-based food production versus acquisition of edible protein and fats from wild seafood."},{"title":"7 Ways to Wean your Child off Video Games","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/7-ways-to-wean-your-child-off-video-games/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/glenn-carstens-peters-204767.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/glenn-carstens-peters-204767.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/jeshoots-com-250229.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/clark-young-143623.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Z2RCL2601T.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Z2RCL2601T-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Z2RCL2601T-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Z2RCL2601T-3.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Z2RCL2601T-4.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_Z2RCL2601T-5.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/iStock-613765102.jpg"],"post_date":"2011-02-09 00:52:09","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":1154,"post_description":"The appeal of today\u2019s ubiquitous video games is based on sound value: the games are fun, the action is fast, the challenges are inviting. Yet when kids and teens spend time in front of small screens \u2013 whether it\u2019s the TV, computer or hand-held games \u2013 it takes away from the time they could spend playing sport, learning other skills</br> or enjoying active play. "},{"title":"Is Gulf Coast Seafood Safe to Eat?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/is-gulf-coast-seafood-safe-to-eat/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/caroline-attwood-301746-1.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/caroline-attwood-301746-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/erwan-hesry-209418.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-11-09 23:32:11","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6401,"post_description":"Gulf residents and seafood industry workers can breathe a collective sigh of relief with the recent reopening of approximately 3,000 square miles of the Gulf to shrimp and fish harvesting."},{"title":"US Legislation Proposes Chemical Safety Reform in Consumer Products","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/us-legislation-proposes-chemical-safety-reform-in-consumer-products/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-615915652.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-615915652.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2010/11/jaelynn-castillo-58131-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2010/11/tim-mossholder-303025.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-11-05 18:57:29","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5958,"post_description":"Manufacturers have created products for every aspect of our modern lifestyles, but the chemicals in some of these products may pose health risks to ourselves and our families. From cell phones, iPods and computers, to household cleaners and furnishings, children\u2019s toys, paints, and many common items we use every day, it is assumed that someone has ensured the safety of their chemical components. But such is not the case."},{"title":"Prenatal Pesticide Exposure May Raise Risk of ADHD in Children","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/prenatal-pesticide-exposure-may-raise-risk-of-adhd-in-children/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/suhyeon-choi-251615.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/suhyeon-choi-251615.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/kelly-sikkema-261146.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/annie-spratt-177697-2.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-11-04 22:36:42","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6055,"post_description":"Researchers have noted a link between prenatal exposure to organophosphate pesticides and attention disorders in children. In a study reported in a recent edition of Environmental Health Perspectives, the effects of prenatal pesticide exposure in children were not significant at the age of 3, but became apparent at age 5."},{"title":"Bottled Teas Low in Health Benefits","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/bottled-teas-low-in-health-benefits/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-179227112.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/iStock-179227112.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/10/matt-hoffman-310311.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-10-13 17:57:47","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":5706,"post_description":"Drinking green or black tea offers a range of health benefits, but health-conscious consumers may not be getting similar benefits from bottled tea drinks. Researchers reported at the National Meeting of the American Chemical Society that many bottled teas contain almost no antioxidants - polyphenols from tea."},{"title":"7 Principles of a Climate-Friendly Diet","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/7-principles-of-a-climate-friendly-diet/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/tim-gouw-165094.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/tim-gouw-165094.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/StockSnap_BY3UR91MPQ.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/bryan-burgos-138613.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/caroline-attwood-243834.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-09-19 20:33:22","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":3626,"post_description":"The link between climate change and the food we eat is direct, critical, and must be acknowledged if we are to make progress in the global fight against climate change. In her groundbreaking book, Diet for a Hot Planet, Anna Lapp\u00e9 makes a convincing case that the entire global food chain may account for roughly one third of what\u2019s heating our planet. "},{"title":"The Salmonella Outbreak: Are Free-Range, Organic Eggs Safer?","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/the-salmonella-outbreak-are-free-range-organic-eggs-safer/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/annie-spratt-143539-2.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/annie-spratt-143539-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/idella-maeland-123655.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-09-16 22:06:26","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2744,"post_description":"As the government oversees a recall of over 500 million eggs due to a salmonella scare, consumers are wondering which eggs are safe and which are best to avoid. Eggs marketed as \u201cfree range,\u201d \u201ccage free,\u201d and \u201corganic\u201d may provide a safer alternative, but understanding these terms will help the consumer make a more informed choice."},{"title":"6 Ways to Reduce Your Exposure to Pesticides","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/6-ways-to-reduce-your-exposure-to-pesticides/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_D0C5D92CD9.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_D0C5D92CD9.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/StockSnap_BY3UR91MPQ.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/07/clem-onojeghuo-108720.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-05-20 23:55:12","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":1303,"post_description":"Pesticides are designed to control the nuisance and damage caused by pests, and have contributed to reducing disease and increasing food production worldwide. But the availability and widespread use of pesticides also has the potential to pose unexpected risks, both directly and indirectly, to our health. "},{"title":"Pesticide Exposure May Increase Risk of ADHD in Children","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/pesticide-exposure-may-increase-risk-of-adhd-in-children/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-598827520.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/09/iStock-598827520.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-05-20 18:04:40","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":4244,"post_description":"A study recently reported in the journal Pediatrics draws a link between exposure to a type of pesticide residue found on commercially grown produce and the incidence of attention-deficit/hyperactivity disorder (ADHD) in children. Children exposed to higher levels of pesticides known as organophosphates could have a higher risk of ADHD. "},{"title":"Nettle Tea \u2013 How to Make a Natural Spring Tonic","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/nettle-tea-how-to-make-a-natural-spring-tonic/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/jorge-garcia-202566-unsplash.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/jorge-garcia-202566-unsplash.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/nettle-plant-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/nettle-tea-2.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/nettle-tea-3.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/nettle-tea-4.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/03/nettle-tea-5.jpg"],"post_date":"2010-03-08 23:55:34","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":11231,"post_description":"Nettle tea is springtime\u2019s natural elixir. One of the earliest green plants to emerge each spring, nettles can be easily brewed into a tea which has healthful, restorative benefits which boost the immune system and awaken the body to spring."},{"title":"Wet Cleaning vs. Dry Cleaning","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/wet-cleaning-vs-dry-cleaning/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/wet-cleaning-vs-dry-cleaning.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/wet-cleaning-vs-dry-cleaning.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/bruno-nascimento-113628-web.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/11/20000112067-000-00_20000112067-web.jpg"],"post_date":"2009-12-20 04:41:35","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":6573,"post_description":"PERC is dangerous to our environment, to animals, to adults and to children. We can be exposed to PERC as easily as through the air we breathe and the water we drink."},{"title":"Formaldehyde Link to Leukemia Confirmed: How to Limit Exposure in the Home","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/formaldehyde-link-to-leukemia-confirmed-how-to-limit-exposure-in-the-home/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia01.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia01.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia04.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia03.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia02.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia04-1.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/leukemia04-2.jpg"],"post_date":"2009-12-02 02:19:15","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":2501,"post_description":"In October 2009, 23 scientists from 6 countries met at the International Agency for Research on Cancer (IARC) to reassess the carcinogenicity of a number of chemical compounds previously classified as carcinogenic to humans."},{"title":"Making Your Own Apple Juice","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/making-your-own-apple-juice/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-597647256.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/iStock-597647256.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/aaron-blanco-tejedor-390113.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2018/01/annie-spratt-124160.jpg"],"post_date":"2009-10-29 20:23:55","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":9302,"post_description":"As anyone who has fruit trees knows, a lot of fruit goes to waste. Woodpecker holes, worm holes, bug damage and bruises occur on a considerable portion of the harvest. Imperfect fruit will not last in storage and can ruin other fruit it is stored with. A great way to avoid this waste is to make your own juice."},{"title":"Vermiculite and Asbestos: How to Minimize the Risks","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/vermiculite-and-asbestos-how-to-minimize-the-risks/","featured_image":"https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-467645332.jpg","additional_images":["https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2017/08/iStock-467645332.jpg","https://eartheasy.local/site-files/2009/04/mca-shield-square.jpg"],"post_date":"2009-04-03 20:26:39","post_category":"Health &amp; Wellness","post_type":"ee_articles","post_id":1816,"post_description":"When we hear the word \"asbestos\" we often think back on the controversy of the late 1970's when it became common knowledge that asbestos was indeed a human health hazard. Since then, many steps have been taken to remove asbestos from buildings and commercial products in an effort to reduce human exposure to this mineral."},{"title":"Healthy Cookware","public_url":"https://eartheasy.local/articles/healthy-cookware/",